ants-terminal (0.6.24-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Status-bar "Add to allowlist" button now persists for the full life
    of the Claude Code permission prompt (was retracted mid-prompt by
    the TUI's own repaint traffic).
  * "Review Changes" disabled state legible on every theme, including
    One Dark and Kanagawa where the previous textSecondary-based fix
    still failed WCAG AA.
  * Extend the main-screen scrollback-doubling suppression window to
    cover `CSI H; CSI 0J` and corner-cursor `CSI 1J` in addition to
    `CSI 2J`. All three sequences produce the same post-state (every
    visible cell cleared) and therefore triggered the same
    scrollback-doubling bug under TUI repaint bursts.

 -- Ants Terminal Contributors <ants-terminal@users.noreply.github.com>  Wed, 15 Apr 2026 16:00:00 +0000

ants-terminal (0.6.23-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix allowlist subsumption false-positive that rejected legitimate
    compound rules like `Bash(make * | tail * && ctest * | tail *)`
    when a simple-prefix rule existed for the first segment.
  * Fix right-click tab colour picker having no visible effect
    (stylesheet specificity beat setTabTextColor).
  * Event-driven status bar: clear transient widgets on tab switch
    so stale Allow buttons / notifications don't cross between tabs.
  * Fix Shift+Enter paste-image regression.
  * SIMD VT-parser ground-state scan (SSE2 / NEON) — bulk Print
    emission on runs of safe printable-ASCII.

 -- Ants Terminal Contributors <ants-terminal@users.noreply.github.com>  Wed, 15 Apr 2026 15:00:00 +0000

ants-terminal (0.6.22-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix main-screen TUI scrollback-doubling regression (root cause:
    Claude Code v2.1+ repaints its entire TUI on every state update,
    filling scrollback with duplicates). Now suppressed via a 250 ms
    sliding window anchored to main-screen CSI 2J.
  * Add debian/postinst and debian/postrm hooks to refresh the icon
    cache and desktop database on install/remove.

 -- Ants Terminal Contributors <ants-terminal@users.noreply.github.com>  Wed, 15 Apr 2026 14:00:00 +0000

